    {
      q: "Is East Beach in Watch Hill free?",
      a: "Yes, the beach itself is free — but access is restricted. There's no public parking near the Watch Hill end. You need to be a Watch Hill Fire District sticker holder, a registered hotel guest, or walk in from Misquamicut State Beach (which has paid parking) to use East Beach.",
    },
    {
      q: "Where do you park for East Beach Watch Hill?",
      a: "There's no public parking lot for East Beach at the Watch Hill end. Options: (1) hotel guests get parking through their property, (2) Fire District sticker holders use restricted residential spots, (3) day visitors park at Misquamicut State Beach ($20–$30 in 2026) and walk west along the shoreline to reach East Beach.",
    },
    {
      q: "Are there lifeguards at East Beach?",
      a: "Lifeguards are only stationed at the Misquamicut State Beach section to the east. The Watch Hill end of East Beach has no lifeguards. Swim at your own risk and stay aware of rip currents on outgoing tides.",
    },
    {
      q: "What's the difference between East Beach and Misquamicut?",
      a: "They're the same continuous shoreline. Misquamicut is the state beach with concessions, lifeguards, parking, restrooms, and the amusement strip across the road. East Beach is the Watch Hill end of the same beach, with no facilities, no lifeguards, restricted parking, and significantly fewer crowds. The transition between them is gradual as you walk along the shoreline.",
    },
    {
      q: "Can you swim at East Beach?",
      a: "Yes — same Atlantic water and same gentle surf as Misquamicut. Water temperatures hit ~65°F by late June and peak around 70°F in August. No lifeguards means you swim at your own risk; the locals' move is to swim near other beachgoers and avoid going alone.",
    },
    {
      q: "Is East Beach better than Misquamicut?",
      a: "It depends on what you want. East Beach is quieter, prettier, and more peaceful, but has no facilities. Misquamicut is busier and more developed, with lifeguards, food, restrooms, and easy parking. For a family with young kids who need facilities, Misquamicut is better. For couples, photographers, and anyone who wants a quiet beach day, East Beach is the choice — if you can figure out the access.",
    },
  ],
  related: [
    { href: "/blog/best-things-to-do-in-watch-hill-ri", tag: "Activities", title: "15 Best Things to Do in Watch Hill" },
    { href: "/blog/misquamicut-state-beach", tag: "Next Door", title: "Misquamicut State Beach Guide" },
